This paper is about natural language processing and machine learning, which are both subfields of computer science. The focus of the paper is on emotion-cause pair extraction, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The proposed method involves multi-task learning and link prediction, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves experiments and evaluation, which are common in information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL, followed by cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, and cs.NE.
